<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Wraven</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Apprentice</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Jun 25, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 13</FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-07-23 10:41&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">Well the guards give bad faction <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif"><BR><BR>Seriously though.  There is one dwarf at Den and friends that will give you bad faction with the guards.  He's the one sitting out by the water holding a fishing pole.  I know a lot of druids don't really care about their faction with Kaladim and go ahead and include him with the 3 others for their quadding.<BR><BR>Also at the docks.  There are 2 dwarves sitting on land next to the ramps leading up to the docks.  You'll want to leave those 2 alone if you're worried about faction.  The 4 you want to kill are at these loctions:<BR>1 is up by the shuttles that leave for FV.  The other up on the dock is by the boat that leaves for antonica.<BR>The other 2 are in the huts over by the left wall.  <BR><BR>What I did was walk up to one of the huts, open the door and depending on your faction with them so far, you may or may not have to aggro them.  If you don't have to aggro them, hopefully both will come running out of their huts.  Take off running outside of the gates and snare one.  Run further and snare the other.  This will leave you enough time to run up to the docks and snare the 2 that are there.  Once you've gotten all 4 snared, round em up inside the gates and proceed to quad kite em inside the walls.<BR><BR>Or if you don't have enough room for your taste, take them outside the gates and quad them out in front.  Just be careful you don't aggro the 2 that are out at the ruins.<BR><BR>Oh..and be prepared to defend your camp.  I've never camped these and not had some asshole come up and either demand to share the spawn with you or try to steal the camp altogether.  Even had one cast nullify magic on my snared dorfs and made me gate out.<BR><BR>There are other places to hunt that yield just as good exp as these dorfs so that might be something to think about.  Now I know you're wondering where...well I'll leave you to find that out on your own.  And these places aren't over camped like the dorfs.<BR><BR>Either way, good luck to ya.<BR><BR><font size=-1>[ This Message was edited by: Wraven on 2001-07-23 10:43 ]</font></FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#e6ebd7"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=646"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Wraven"></a>
